ault": false, "description": "Area: Rustdoc's search feature"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2023-05-28T15:54:47Z", "updated_at": "2023-05-28T16:00:08Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Often features features are coded with jargon or unique keywords that are nonetheless elaborate by comments or examples with other phrases. `Search` does not appear to include those text and so misses being as useful as it needs to be. For instance, `clap.rs` has a `debug_assert` for \"Catch problems earlier in the development cycle\". Recalling and subsequently finding the description of this feature in `docs.rs` was very difficult. Unless you remember part of `debug_assert` feature name, you were out of luck using other phrases associated with the included example such as \"test\" and \"verify\".\r\n\r\nPerhaps a secondary indexing system can be established to collect less common phrases associated with items and features and used to provide a secondary set of results.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/112044/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/112044/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}